#: ../../source/security.rst:2
msgid "Security Design"
msgstr "安全設計"

#: ../../source/security.rst:4
msgid "Read :ref:`how_it_works` first to get a handle on how BurnBox works."
msgstr "首先閱讀:ref:`how_it_works` 來了解基礎的 BurnBox 運作原理。"

#: ../../source/security.rst:6
msgid "Like all software, BurnBox may contain bugs or vulnerabilities."
msgstr "就像所有的應用程式，BurnBox 可能有錯誤或弱點。"

#: ../../source/security.rst:9
msgid "What BurnBox protects against"
msgstr "BurnBox 保護與防止"

#: ../../source/security.rst:11
msgid ""
"**Third parties don't have access to anything that happens in BurnBox.** "
"Using BurnBox means hosting services directly on your computer. When "
"sharing your files with BurnBox, they are not uploaded to any third-party "
"server. If you make an BurnBox chat room, your computer acts as a server "
"for that too. This avoids the traditional model of having to trust the "
"computers of others."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/security.rst:17
msgid ""
"**Network eavesdroppers can't spy on anything that happens in BurnBox in "
"transit.** The connection between the Tor onion service and Tor Browser is "
"end-to-end encrypted. This means network attackers can't eavesdrop on "
"anything except encrypted Tor traffic. Even if an eavesdropper is a "
"malicious rendezvous node used to connect the Tor Browser with BurnBox's "
"onion service, the traffic is encrypted using the onion service's private "
"key."
msgstr ""
"**網路竊聽者無法偵察 BurnBox 傳輸中發生的情況。** Tor 洋蔥服務與 Tor 瀏覽"
"器之間的連接為端到端加密，這代表 網路攻擊者除了加密的 Tor 流量無法竊聽任何東"
"西，即便攻擊者是 Tor 瀏覽器與 BurnBox 洋蔥服務連接的惡意會合節點，其流量也"
"使用洋蔥服務私鑰加密。"

#: ../../source/security.rst:23
msgid ""
"**Anonymity of BurnBox users are protected by Tor.** BurnBox and Tor "
"Browser protect the anonymity of the users. As long as the BurnBox user "
"anonymously communicates the BurnBox address with the Tor Browser users, "
"the Tor Browser users and eavesdroppers can't learn the identity of the "
"BurnBox user."
msgstr ""
"**BurnBox 使用者的匿名受到 Tor 保護。** BurnBox 與 Tor 瀏覽器保護使用者"
"匿名，只要使用 BurnBox 地址與 Tor 瀏覽器進行匿名通訊，Tor 瀏覽器使用者與竊"
"聽者無法知道 BurnBox 使用者的身份。"

#: ../../source/security.rst:28
msgid ""
"**If an attacker learns about the onion service, they still can't access "
"anything.** Prior attacks against the Tor network to enumerate onion "
"services allowed attackers to discover private ``.onion`` addresses. To "
"access an BurnBox service from its address, the private key used for "
"client authentication must be guessed (unless the service is already made "
"public by turning off the private key -- see :ref:`turn_off_private_key`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/security.rst:33
msgid "What BurnBox doesn't protect against"
msgstr "BurnBox 無法保護的部份"

#: ../../source/security.rst:35
msgid ""
"**Communicating the BurnBox address and private key might not be secure."
"** Communicating the BurnBox address to people is the responsibility of "
"the BurnBox user. If sent insecurely (such as through an e-mail message "
"monitored by an attacker), an eavesdropper can tell that BurnBox is being "
"used. Eavesdroppers can access services that are still up by loading their "
"addresses and/or lost key in the Tor Browser. Avoid this by communicating "
"the address securely, via encrypted text message (probably with disappearing "
"messages enabled), encrypted e-mail, or in person. This isn't necessary when "
"using BurnBox for something that isn't secret."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/security.rst:42
msgid ""
"**Communicating the BurnBox address and private key might not be "
"anonymous.** Extra precaution must be taken to ensure the BurnBox address "
"is communicated anonymously. A new e-mail or chat account, only accessed "
"over Tor, can be used to share the address. This isn't necessary unless "
"anonymity is a goal."
msgstr ""
